    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 CPB hemolysis prediction is accepted at Medium assurance level. Seven of thirteen credibility factors were formally assessed; all assessed factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors were scoped out or not-assessed per MRL 2 requirements for Class II devices. The CFD model demonstrates adequate predictive capability for hemolysis index QoI with mean absolute error of 8.7% against FDA benchmark data. All RH values satisfy the RH < 1 acceptance criterion across five operating points. Discretization error is well-characterized with GCI below 5%. Model form, input parameters, and validation relevance are all adequately established for the intended regulatory use. The assessment team concludes the model is fit for purpose to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the CPB device submission.",
